# Backend Security and Alerting Rules

Token rules:
- Raw ingestion tokens are returned only once at creation.
- Store only token hashes plus safe token prefixes.
- Never log raw tokens.
- Never return raw tokens from list/detail endpoints.
- Validate ingestion with `X-Ingestion-Token`, not JWT bearer auth.

Webhook rules:
- Webhook URLs may be stored because the backend needs them for delivery.
- Never log full webhook URLs.
- Never return full webhook URLs from GET/list endpoints.
- Return masked URLs only when useful.

Alert MVP rules:
- Log ingestion should not fail just because alert delivery fails.
- INFO/WARN logs should not alert unless explicitly requested.
- ERROR logs go into lightweight in-memory aggregation.
- The scheduler drains buckets on the configured interval and sends one summarized alert per bucket to enabled Slack/Discord destinations.
- Do not add Kafka, RabbitMQ, Redis, Elasticsearch, or persistent log storage for this MVP.
